  "description": "From the manufacturer About Us Sidney's father was a cabinetmaker and his mother funded the business venture with 50 pounds. During the second world war the first night raid destroyed the original 1932 factory and the business moved to its present location in Cricklewood, London. Ronnie Rustin, Sidney's son, took over the business and ran it until his death in 2008. He drove the growth of Rustins to be one of the good brands in the industry with a focus on wood finishing products, speciality paints and decorating sundries. Rustins EWDOIL500 Exterior Wood Oil 500ml A water-borne blend of natural plant oils and other ingredients to nourish and protect all types of outdoor timber which dries with a low lustre finish. It is a penetrating oil drying to a hard durable and water resistant seal that brings out the beauty of the grain within the timber. Rustins Exterior Wood Oil confirms to The Articles in Contract with Food Regulations. Can be used for both interior and exterior application. Clean brushes with water.",
